1
00:00:40,203 --> 00:00:43,043
It's been a while, Okkotsu.

2
00:00:44,093 --> 00:00:46,303
Stay away.

3
00:00:46,283 --> 00:00:49,973
Oh, come on. Don't play hard to get.

4
00:00:49,973 --> 00:00:52,593
m -960 -201 l 960 -201 960 603 -960 603

5
00:00:49,973 --> 00:00:52,593
I said don't

6
00:00:50,923 --> 00:00:52,593
You can't.

7
00:00:53,173 --> 00:00:56,263
Do you have any idea 
how bad I've wanted to slug you?

8
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:59,723
Try to understand my feelings!

9
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:01,983
m -960 -201 l 960 -201 960 603 -960 603

10
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:01,983
Stop it

11
00:01:00,513 --> 00:01:01,983
Stop.

12
00:01:01,973 --> 00:01:06,773
If you keep me on edge like this, 
I might just end up killing you.

13
00:01:07,223 --> 00:01:09,243
Don't do it, Rika{**-chan}!

14
00:01:10,783 --> 00:01:12,113
Rika?

15
00:01:12,913 --> 00:01:16,913
m -960 -201 l 960 -201 960 603 -960 603

16
00:01:12,913 --> 00:01:16,913
Record: November 2016, Tokyo

17
00:01:20,743 --> 00:01:22,173
I'm sorry.

18
00:01:22,993 --> 00:01:24,283
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:25,993 --> 00:01:28,843
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

20
00:01:28,843 --> 00:01:31,173
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

21
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:34,183
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

22
00:01:53,243 --> 00:01:56,663
A complete cover-up and a secret execution?

23
00:01:56,663 --> 00:01:57,993
That's ridiculous.

24
00:01:58,793 --> 00:02:01,113
The boy himself has consented to it.

25
00:02:02,213 --> 00:02:05,793
He's underage. Just sixteen years old.

26
00:02:06,383 --> 00:02:09,323
You're afraid of how many he might curse to death.

27
00:02:10,173 --> 00:02:15,683
He has already turned the tables on 
three second-grades and even a first-grade.

28
00:02:16,093 --> 00:02:18,753
That's why you've turned to me.

29
00:02:20,643 --> 00:02:22,353
Have you forgotten that?

30
00:02:24,023 --> 00:02:25,353
Then are you suggesting...

31
00:02:25,353 --> 00:02:26,903
Indeed. {You guessed it.}

32
00:02:26,903 --> 00:02:31,313
We'll be taking Okkotsu Yuta into Jujutsu Tech.

33
00:02:34,993 --> 00:02:38,783
Do you mind explaining what this is, Okkotsu Yuta{**-kun}?

34
00:02:39,863 --> 00:02:42,543
It's a knife... or at least it used to be.

35
00:02:44,413 --> 00:02:46,293
I tried to kill myself...

36
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:50,923
but Rika{**-chan} wouldn't let me.

37
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:53,263
That's dark.

38
00:02:56,263 --> 00:02:58,473
You're starting at a new school today.

39
00:02:59,393 --> 00:03:00,723
I'm not going.

40
00:03:04,053 --> 00:03:06,773
I don't want to hurt anyone anymore. {again}

41
00:03:07,313 --> 00:03:10,113
So I'm never going outside again. {So I won't be going outside anymore.}

42
00:03:11,323 --> 00:03:12,363
But...{actually entire line could just be the first word.}

43
00:03:12,783 --> 00:03:14,993
it gets lonely all by yourself.{starting with capital letter after ellipses?}

44
00:03:18,363 --> 00:03:25,253
Depending on how it's used, 
the curse placed on you can save people as well.

45
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:25,253
Tokyo Jujutsu High School{cut?}

46
00:03:26,413 --> 00:03:28,623
Learn to use that power.

47
00:03:29,383 --> 00:03:34,053
After that, you're free to decide 
whether it's worth throwing everything away.{whether WHAT is worth throwing everything away for? I know it's supposed to be rhetorical, but this implies a missing element. Ideally, line will have few more words: "You're free to decide whether it's worth it - to throw everything else away." Alternatively, I prefer: "After that, you're free to decide whether throwing everything away is worth it."}

