1370
00:06:35,653 --> 00:06:36,693
He killed them?

1371
00:06:36,693 --> 00:06:37,733
Tuna mayo?

1372
00:06:38,113 --> 00:06:40,143
Nope, but gravely injured, apparently.{grammatically, my edit does not sit well with me. Would prefer removing the final word. All this because commas work as pauses even while reading, effectively increasing the CPS. So I feel this line flies by too fast with its 2 comma-state.}

1373
00:06:41,783 --> 00:06:44,363
Well, if he's too cocky, I'll put him in his place.

1374
00:06:44,743 --> 00:06:45,853
Bonito flakes.

1375
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,893
Listen up, everyone!

1376
00:06:48,893 --> 00:06:50,263
Transfer student!{replace excalmation mark with dash, emdash, ellipses, or nothing at all, and remove caps on next line. Feels like one neat sentence.} {the whole point is it needs to feel separated, like the way he said it.}

1377
00:06:50,263 --> 00:06:51,243
Incoming!

1378
00:06:51,243 --> 00:06:54,253
Let's all give him a hand!

1379
00:06:56,963 --> 00:06:58,253
Not one hand...

1380
00:06:59,363 --> 00:07:01,753
I heard he's a real wet blanket.

1381
00:07:02,383 --> 00:07:05,843
Hard to get excited about welcoming someone like that.

1382
00:07:06,303 --> 00:07:07,183
Salmon.{add a line for Panda's "Mmhm" please. Is not a non-dialog grunt, it IS his line.}

1383
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:08,393
Right...

1384
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:12,973
Moving on!{completes his previous ellipses break}{this is a totally different line...}

1385
00:07:14,353 --> 00:07:15,813
Come on in!

1386
00:07:16,273 --> 00:07:19,523
I sense a really damp mood in there.

1387
00:07:25,863 --> 00:07:27,533
I'll just ignore him.{Feels like a light prediction, instead of a solid decision. "I'm just going to ignore him." sounds motivated. "I will just ignore him" miiiiight be better, if you get what I mean. how about... "I think I'm just gonna ignore him."?}

1388
00:07:44,383 --> 00:07:45,593
I'm Okkotsu Yut—

1389
00:07:47,473 --> 00:07:49,343
Is this a surprise test?

1390
00:07:51,473 --> 00:07:52,603
You.

1391
00:07:54,043 --> 00:07:56,853
You're cursed.

1392
00:07:57,313 --> 00:07:59,693
This is a place to learn about curses.

1393
00:07:59,693 --> 00:08:02,773
Not a place for the cursed to be. {do i remove italics?}

1394
00:08:05,643 --> 00:08:12,453
More than ten thousand unexplained deaths and 
missing persons are reported annually across the country.

1395
00:08:12,443 --> 00:08:19,373
Most of them are a result of curses 
born from the negative emotions of people.

1396
00:08:19,373 --> 00:08:22,713
Among them are also some malicious cases caused by curse users.{no capitalizing Curse Users?}{aaaaaaaaaa the terminology confusion strikes again. in the style guide we've decided not to capitalize jujutsu sorceres so this will follow the same rules}

1397
00:08:23,173 --> 00:08:26,953
You need curses to fight curses.

1398
00:08:27,593 --> 00:08:30,343
And this is where we learn 
about curses to exorcise curses:

1399
00:08:30,963 --> 00:08:33,853
Tokyo Jujutsu Technical High School.

1400
00:08:36,223 --> 00:08:38,353
You're just telling me that now?

1401
00:08:40,693 --> 00:08:42,483
You're just telling him that now?

1402
00:08:43,153 --> 00:08:44,473
My bad!

1403
00:08:44,473 --> 00:08:47,303
Oh, I'd back away real quick if I were you.

1404
00:08:53,743 --> 00:08:56,443
Do not...

1405
00:08:56,443 --> 00:08:58,453
Wait! Rika{**-chan}!

1406
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:02,883
...bully Yuta!

1407
00:09:02,883 --> 00:09:08,883
m -960 -201 l 960 -201 960 603 -960 603

1408
00:09:02,883 --> 00:09:05,883
Special-Grade Cursed Human
Special-Grade Vengeful Spirit

1409
00:09:02,883 --> 00:09:05,883
Okkotsu Yuta
Orimoto Rika

1410
00:09:05,883 --> 00:09:08,883
Record: Six Years Ago, Sendai City, Miyagi Prefecture

1411
00:09:12,883 --> 00:09:14,253
Over there! Check it out!

1412
00:09:14,253 --> 00:09:15,503
Oh! What is it?

1413
00:09:17,523 --> 00:09:20,273
Happy birthday, Yuta!

1414
00:09:24,483 --> 00:09:27,153
Whoa! Can I open it?

1415
00:09:27,153 --> 00:09:28,443
Go ahead.

1416
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:30,273
Really? I can open it?!

1417
00:09:30,273 --> 00:09:31,703
Just do it already!

1418
00:09:37,623 --> 00:09:39,203
A ring?

1419
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:41,543
It's an engagement ring.

1420
00:09:41,543 --> 00:09:42,713
What's that?

1421
00:09:55,093 --> 00:09:56,473
It's a promise.

1422
00:09:57,603 --> 00:10:01,873
A promise that when we grow up, we'll get married.

1423
00:10:06,903 --> 00:10:07,923
Is this real?!

1424
00:10:08,473 --> 00:10:11,313
Hey! Someone call an ambulance!

1425
00:10:11,313 --> 00:10:15,283
Idiot! Just look at her! It's too late!

1426
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:13,323
Are they okay?

1427
00:10:15,293 --> 00:10:16,983
Her head's crushed in!

1428
00:10:16,983 --> 00:10:18,333
But... I mean...

1429
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:22,583
A child got run over by a car! Yes! Hurry!

1430
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,583
This is messed up!

1431
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,583
I'm not going near that!

1432
00:10:28,003 --> 00:10:29,463
Rika{**-chan}?

1433
00:10:31,053 --> 00:10:33,803
Yuta...

1434
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:44,603
Yuta.

1435
00:10:45,523 --> 00:10:48,973
When we grow up,

1436
00:10:48,973 --> 00:10:53,853
we'll get married!

1437
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,373
It's a promise.{AAA I want this to be an exclamation mark to match her voice, then you'd also have to change the previous instance in line 89. But I know, the finality of a period in this black screen...}

1438
00:10:59,583 --> 00:11:00,993
As you can see,

1439
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:04,623
he's been cursed by Rika{**-chan}, 
who is madly in love with him!

1440
00:11:04,903 --> 00:11:07,673
Let's welcome Okkotsu Yuta!

1441
00:11:07,673 --> 00:11:10,383
Be nice to him, everyone!{I want to rearrange to "Everyone, be nice to him!" I think it ends well with "him" as the camera lands on him. Matching the japanese order doesn't hurt.}

1442
00:11:12,053 --> 00:11:16,583
Remember that attacking Yuta will activate Rika{**-chan}'s curse.

1443
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:19,553
Or maybe it won't. Be careful either way!

1444
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:22,183
Should've said it sooner.

1445
00:11:23,023 --> 00:11:26,943
Since they're being so rebellious, 
let me make some quick introductions.

1446
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,313
I have a feeling this teacher is to blame.

1447
00:11:30,813 --> 00:11:33,403
This is the cursed tool user, Zenin Maki.

1448
00:11:33,403 --> 00:11:36,263
She uses special tools to exorcise curses.

1449
00:11:37,313 --> 00:11:39,993
This is the Cursed Speech user, Inumaki Toge.

1450
00:11:39,993 --> 00:11:43,663
He can only speak in rice ball ingredients, 
so good luck talking to him!

1451
00:11:43,663 --> 00:11:44,443
Kelp.

1452
00:11:44,443 --> 00:11:45,753
This is Panda.

1453
00:11:45,753 --> 00:11:46,753
I'm Panda.

1454
00:11:46,753 --> 00:11:48,423
Nice to meet you.

1455
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,883
Well, there you have it.

1456
00:11:51,173 --> 00:11:53,923
He didn't give me the explanation I wanted most!

1457
00:11:54,883 --> 00:11:58,183
All right! Our first-year class is a solid four students!{lmao "is a solid four-" becomes a value based assignment. Like "She's a solid ten." So, I wonder if this can be phrased differently. "Our first-year class is a solid batch of four!"? group of four students? that may be too long.}

1458
00:11:59,183 --> 00:12:01,853
Three students and one animal, anyway.

1459
00:12:02,393 --> 00:12:04,313
For your afternoon jujutsu practice,

1460
00:12:04,643 --> 00:12:06,933
you'll be working in pairs!

1461
00:12:07,353 --> 00:12:09,063
Toge and Panda, pair up.

1462
00:12:09,063 --> 00:12:10,013
Let's do this.

1463
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,653
Maki and Yuta, pair up.

1464
00:12:12,653 --> 00:12:13,193
Yikes!

1465
00:12:14,153 --> 00:12:15,533
Did she just say "yikes"?!

1466
00:12:21,493 --> 00:12:22,913
U-Um...

1467
00:12:22,913 --> 00:12:25,663
I-I'm looking forward to working together.

1468
00:12:28,123 --> 00:12:30,673
You were bullied, weren't you?

1469
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:38,053
Thought so.

1470
00:12:38,053 --> 00:12:40,673
I totally get it. Even I'd bully you.

1471
00:12:41,463 --> 00:12:43,553
Maybe you do it because of the curse,

1472
00:12:43,553 --> 00:12:47,733
but that good guy act you got plastered all over your face, it's disgusting.

1473
00:12:48,983 --> 00:12:52,403
Why are you playing the victim 
when you're the one being protected?

1474
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,983
I bet you've been passive your whole life.

1475
00:12:56,323 --> 00:12:58,993
You think you can get by just like that?

1476
00:12:59,903 --> 00:13:02,113
You're underestimating Jujutsu Tech.

1477
00:13:04,113 --> 00:13:06,403
That's enough, Maki.

1478
00:13:06,403 --> 00:13:07,793
Bonito flakes!

1479
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:12,173
All right, fine! Get off my case.

1480
00:13:12,623 --> 00:13:13,963
Sorry about that.

1481
00:13:13,963 --> 00:13:17,663
She has a bad habit of 
making assumptions about people. {acting like she understands others} {jumping to conclusions} {>females}

1482
00:13:18,123 --> 00:13:19,263
It's fine.

1483
00:13:20,263 --> 00:13:22,253
She's not wrong.

1484
00:13:28,173 --> 00:13:29,103
Where are we?

1485
00:13:29,103 --> 00:13:31,063
It's just an elementary school.

1486
00:13:31,063 --> 00:13:31,643
Oh?

1487
00:13:31,643 --> 00:13:36,113
Just another elementary school where some kids have gone missing.

1488
00:13:36,103 --> 00:13:37,723
Wait, what?!

1489
00:13:38,113 --> 00:13:40,033
It happens in places like this.

1490
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:44,163
Probably the handiwork of a naturally occurring curse.

1491
00:13:44,783 --> 00:13:48,163
You're saying they were kidnapped by a curse?

1492
00:13:48,163 --> 00:13:50,873
Yup, two that we know of.

1493
00:13:50,873 --> 00:13:56,503
Curses tend to manifest in crowded places 
that many people have memories of.{crowded places feel like a very temporal thing. Places are crowded only for moments. "densely-populated places" would be perfect.} {that'd mean something else entirely}

1494
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:04,643
Places like schools and hospitals are often associated with negative emotions.

1495
00:14:05,143 --> 00:14:10,343
As those emotions build up, 
they give birth to curses like the one here.

1496
00:14:10,343 --> 00:14:13,483
Exorcise the curse. Rescue the children.

1497
00:14:13,483 --> 00:14:15,063
And retrieve them if they're dead.

1498
00:14:16,483 --> 00:14:17,823
They could be dead?

1499
00:14:19,323 --> 00:14:22,653
Emerge from the darkness that is darker than black.{lmao okay}

1500
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,823
Purify that which is impure.

1501
00:14:30,043 --> 00:14:31,623
It's getting dark.

1502
00:14:32,993 --> 00:14:34,663
It's a Veil.

1503
00:14:34,663 --> 00:14:40,173
It's a barrier that will smoke out the curse 
and keep you guys concealed from the outside.

1504
00:14:41,843 --> 00:14:44,383
You can easily undo it from the inside!

1505
00:14:46,713 --> 00:14:51,183
Now, do be careful not to die on us.

1506
00:14:51,603 --> 00:14:53,063
Wait...

1507
00:14:53,063 --> 00:14:54,023
{*}Sir{*Sensei}!

1508
00:14:54,023 --> 00:14:55,393
Hey, transfer student.

1509
00:14:56,553 --> 00:14:58,513
Don't {let yourself}get distracted.

1510
00:15:03,963 --> 00:15:05,573
Put... me... on?

1511
00:15:05,573 --> 00:15:07,663
Put... me... on?

1512
00:15:07,663 --> 00:15:08,873
Put... me... on?

1513
00:15:12,493 --> 00:15:15,413
Put me on?

1514
