2902
00:55:01,713 --> 00:55:05,553
As well as the Holy Land of Jujutsu, Kyoto.

2903
00:55:05,543 --> 00:55:08,303
A thousand curses will be unleashed upon each location.

2904
00:55:08,303 --> 00:55:11,563
Their sole command, of course, will be to massacre. {dis correct?}{ye}

2905
00:55:11,563 --> 00:55:17,023
If you wish to avoid a scene straight out of hell, 
put your lives on the line and fight.

2906
00:55:17,313 --> 00:55:21,613
Let us curse each other to our heart's content!

2907
00:55:28,083 --> 00:55:29,083
{*}Master Geto{*Geto-sama}!

2908
00:55:29,453 --> 00:55:31,163
The cafe is gonna close!

2909
00:55:31,163 --> 00:55:32,913
It's already that late?

2910
00:55:33,333 --> 00:55:34,973
I'm sorry, Satoru.

2911
00:55:35,423 --> 00:55:39,243
The girls insist on trying the crepes from Takeshita Street. {gotta remove the accents because we don't do that in other places like character names}

2912
00:55:39,243 --> 00:55:41,173
Hurry!

2913
00:55:41,173 --> 00:55:43,303
I'll be taking my leave now.

2914
00:55:43,303 --> 00:55:46,793
Man, I don't get what's so great about 
a place filled with monkeys.

2915
00:55:46,793 --> 00:55:49,013
What makes you think we'd just let you leave?

2916
00:55:50,663 --> 00:55:52,023
You don't wanna do that.

2917
00:55:59,983 --> 00:56:02,533
Your precious students are all within my range.

2918
00:56:05,193 --> 00:56:07,613
Well then, everyone, see you on the battlefield. {Well then, see you all on the battlefield!}{To reduce two pauses to one. Also the line flies past too fast for two pauses.}{but it's perfectly readable :/}

2919
00:56:21,503 --> 00:56:23,343
Survival of the weakest.

2920
00:56:23,883 --> 00:56:26,923
That's the ideal form society should take.

2921
00:56:26,923 --> 00:56:30,303
Help the weak and keep the strong in check.

2922
00:56:30,303 --> 00:56:31,933
Listen to me, Satoru.

2923
00:56:31,933 --> 00:56:34,933
Sorcerers exist to protect non-sorcerers.

2924
00:56:34,933 --> 00:56:39,693
Look at you, acting all righteous. I hate that stuff.

2925
00:56:42,563 --> 00:56:46,323
Are you the strongest because you're Gojo Satoru?

2926
00:56:46,323 --> 00:56:49,283
Or are you Gojo Satoru because you're the strongest?

2927
00:56:49,283 --> 00:56:51,033
What exactly are you getting at?

2928
00:56:51,453 --> 00:56:57,753
If I could be you, wouldn't my foolish ideals 
become reasonable possibilities?

2929
00:57:01,043 --> 00:57:03,043
This is the path I've chosen.

2930
00:57:03,043 --> 00:57:06,673
All that's left is to follow it to the best of my ability.

2931
00:57:45,883 --> 00:57:47,203
Geto Suguru.

2932
00:57:47,703 --> 00:57:51,093
A special-grade curse user who uses Curse Manipulation.

2933
00:57:51,093 --> 00:57:56,263
He can draw in and manipulate 
naturally occurring unbound curses.

2934
00:57:57,013 --> 00:58:02,603
It seems he has established a religious group 
to collect curses from its followers.

2935
00:58:03,403 --> 00:58:06,433
He should still have the ones he previously possessed,

2936
00:58:06,433 --> 00:58:11,613
and considering the decline in the 
number of curses reported in recent years,

2937
00:58:12,613 --> 00:58:16,113
his claim to possess two thousand may not be a bluff.

2938
00:58:16,113 --> 00:58:20,623
Statistically speaking, most of them 
have to be weaklings at second grade or lower.

2939
00:58:20,623 --> 00:58:24,963
And even with a generous estimate, 
there can't be more than fifty curse users.

2940
00:58:24,963 --> 00:58:28,173
That's actually the scary part.

2941
00:58:28,173 --> 00:58:31,383
I find it hard to believe he'd start a war he couldn't win.

2942
00:58:31,763 --> 00:58:33,303
God damn!{I died}

2943
00:58:33,303 --> 00:58:38,923
Put out a call for aid to all alumni. 
Alert the Three Great Clans and the Ainu Jujutsu Society.

2944
00:58:38,923 --> 00:58:40,433
It's all-out war!

2945
00:58:41,233 --> 00:58:46,433
This time, we will exorcise this curse named Geto!

2946
00:58:46,433 --> 00:58:50,193
That's probably what the 
meathead principal is saying right now.

2947
00:58:50,193 --> 00:58:56,203
m -960 -201 l 960 -201 960 603 -960 603

2948
00:58:52,243 --> 00:58:56,203
December 24th, 
Day of the Night Parade of a Hundred Demons

2949
00:59:00,663 --> 00:59:07,423
If we seriously tried to kill each other, 
our chance of success would be about thirty percent.

2950
00:59:11,923 --> 00:59:16,933
If the Jujutsu Society gets involved, 
that goes down to less than twenty percent.

2951
00:59:17,303 --> 00:59:22,933
However, there is one move 
which makes that slim chance of victory

2952
00:59:23,393 --> 00:59:25,443
jump straight to ninety-nine percent.

2953
00:59:26,233 --> 00:59:32,443
That is to kill Okkotsu Yuta and take the special-grade vengeful spirit, Orimoto Rika.

2954
00:59:33,493 --> 00:59:38,453
They still believe my bluff from my time in school. {i'm guessing the bluff here is he said he'll kill all non-sorcerers? he did say it back when he was in school too}

2955
00:59:38,873 --> 00:59:41,703
It doesn't matter if the cursed spirit is bound or not.

2956
00:59:41,703 --> 00:59:46,833
As long as I kill the master, I can absorb any curse I want.

2957
00:59:47,953 --> 00:59:53,423
With such high odds of victory,
 they won't risk putting Okkotsu on the battlefield.

2958
00:59:53,423 --> 00:59:57,223
After all, there is a chance 
he could wipe out both enemies and allies.

2959
00:59:57,973 --> 01:00:02,843
The true objective of the Night Parade of a Hundred Demons is to isolate Okkotsu.

2960
01:00:04,853 --> 01:00:08,273
At long last, it's the dawn of a new age.

2961
01:00:11,733 --> 01:00:13,323
It seems like...

2962
01:00:14,993 --> 01:00:17,493
something crazy is going down.

2963
01:00:19,703 --> 01:00:21,203
Maki{**-san}!

2964
01:00:21,203 --> 01:00:24,113
What are you doing here? 
Classes are canceled for the week.

2965
01:00:24,113 --> 01:00:26,713
Well, I was just feeling kinda restless.

2966
01:00:27,833 --> 01:00:30,293
Nobody's at the dorms, either.

2967
01:00:30,293 --> 01:00:34,013
The second-years were dispatched to Kyoto earlier.

2968
01:00:34,013 --> 01:00:37,433
Toge is in Shinjuku as backup,
along with the third- and fourth-years. {there are fourth years???} {fushiguro mentioned it used to be a 4-year school at some point}{less pauses, reads faster, less awkward guessing at hyphen}{nope, revert, but i will simplify it a bit}

2969
01:00:37,433 --> 01:00:41,763
And since the principal likes Panda so much,
 he's probably with Toge as well.

2970
01:00:41,763 --> 01:00:42,763
I see.

2971
01:00:48,103 --> 01:00:49,023
Ask away.

2972
01:00:49,903 --> 01:00:51,523
You've been wondering, right?

2973
01:00:51,523 --> 01:00:53,613
About why I'm called a failure.

2974
01:00:54,283 --> 01:00:58,103
Well, um... yes. {yeah}

2975
01:01:01,703 --> 01:01:07,293
My family, the Zenin clan, is one of the elite sorcerer families known as the Three Great Clans.

2976
01:01:07,793 --> 01:01:12,133
Do you know what's the minimum requirement to be a sorcerer?

2977
01:01:12,133 --> 01:01:13,923
Uh, I'm not sure.

2978
01:01:16,423 --> 01:01:18,263
It's being able to see curses.

2979
01:01:18,263 --> 01:01:19,433
Oh, right.

2980
01:01:20,133 --> 01:01:25,013
Ordinary people can sometimes see them in certain situations, like if they're on the verge of death.

2981
01:01:25,513 --> 01:01:28,943
I can't see curses without these lame glasses, though.

2982
01:01:29,353 --> 01:01:32,693
The cursed tools I use are 
already infused with cursed energy.

2983
01:01:32,693 --> 01:01:34,813
It doesn't come from me.

2984
01:01:36,563 --> 01:01:39,073
At least it gave me an 
excuse to get out of the family!

2985
01:01:39,493 --> 01:01:44,453
The food was awful, the rooms were cramped, and it was crawling with old men I didn't know.

2986
01:01:44,453 --> 01:01:46,543
The whole thing totally sucked!

2987
01:01:48,613 --> 01:01:50,123
Don't use my last name!

2988
01:01:50,123 --> 01:01:54,843
Not everyone has resistance to curses like you do.

2989
01:01:54,843 --> 01:01:57,213
Don't ask me about cursed energy.

2990
01:02:01,183 --> 01:02:04,353
Why do you continue being a sorcerer, then?

2991
01:02:04,353 --> 01:02:06,763
Because I've got a personality problem. {can relate}{personalitits}

2992
01:02:07,433 --> 01:02:11,193
Imagine someone who can't even see curses
 becoming a first-grade sorcerer. {>}{?}

2993
01:02:11,693 --> 01:02:14,443
Can't wait to see the reactions on their faces!

2994
01:02:14,893 --> 01:02:18,443
After that, I'll crush the Zenin clan from within! {bruh :skull:}

2995
01:02:22,363 --> 01:02:23,663
What?

2996
01:02:23,663 --> 01:02:27,083
Oh, I was just thinking that's so like you.

2997
01:02:27,953 --> 01:02:29,143
You know...

2998
01:02:30,543 --> 01:02:32,333
I want to be just like you.

2999
01:02:32,963 --> 01:02:35,263
I want to be strong and unyielding.

3000
01:02:43,383 --> 01:02:46,683
